messages.msgSnippet: ... I was quoted, but I must ve made a typo because I meant a JOG around the store and it says job  Oooops That s here:
messages.messageBody:
On May 6, 2006, at 6:01 PM, Joyce Fetteroll wrote:

> I've added a few new questions and answers to my unschooling website.
>
> http://home.earthlink.net/~fetteroll/rejoycing/
>
> There are even a few people other than me quoted there now :-)

I was quoted, but I must've made a typo because I meant a JOG around
the store and it says "job" Oooops


That's here:

http://home.earthlink.net/~fetteroll/rejoycing/changing%20parenting/
mindfulreplacements.html

I wondered what the stars were! Cool.

Joyce, I had quoted you on a page too, something you put up there.
<g> I don't think it's a bad thing at all for a great response to be
available in two or three places (the original list or forum and
another couple of "best parts" places.

I like your title "arguments against the arguments against TV."

I'm going to link some of your new pages to some of my old pages.

I keep saying I just love your site, but I keep just loving it.

Sandra

messages.messageBody:
I've added a few new questions and answers to my unschooling website.

http://home.earthlink.net/~fetteroll/rejoycing/

There are even a few people other than me quoted there now :-)

(I hope no one minds being quoted. If you do, let me know and I can
remove your name or make it less identifiable. If I didn't identify
you well enough, let me know that too! :-)

Joyce
